# Autopsy — Project Rules (CTO Spec)

## What This Project Is
Autopsy is an AI-powered web application that analyzes Replicated Troubleshoot support bundles (.tar.gz archives of Kubernetes cluster diagnostics). It accepts a bundle upload, extracts and parses the contents, runs a multi-phase Claude-powered analysis, and presents findings via a streaming web dashboard with chat interface.

## Project Name
The project is named **Autopsy**. All references to "BundleIQ" in code, comments, templates, and documentation must use "Autopsy" instead.
- Go module: `github.com/yourusername/autopsy`
- Binary name: `autopsy`
- Docker image: `autopsy:latest`

## Stack (non-negotiable)
- **Language:** Go 1.22+
- **HTTP:** stdlib `net/http` only — no Gin, Echo, or Chi
- **Frontend:** Go `html/template` + HTMX (CDN) + Tailwind CSS (CDN) — zero JS build step
- **AI:** `github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-go` — official SDK only
- **Streaming:** Server-Sent Events (SSE) via `net/http` + HTMX SSE extension
- **No database:** in-memory session store with mutex, TTL cleanup goroutine
- **Live reload dev:** `air` (github.com/air-verse/air)
- **Container:** Docker (multi-stage build) + docker-compose for one-command run

