## Commit Strategy
**After every story completes, Cursor MUST:**
1. `git add -A`
2. `git commit -m "feat(SX.Y): <story description>"`
   - Use conventional commits format
   - Epic prefix: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `docs`
   - Story ID matches the STORIES.md numbering
3. Never batch multiple stories into one commit
4. If a story adds tests, tests must pass before commit

## Docker Requirements (non-negotiable)
- The app MUST be fully runnable via `docker-compose up` — no Go installation required by the reviewer
- Dockerfile uses a **multi-stage build**: `golang:1.22-alpine` builder → `alpine:3.19` runtime
- Final image must be under 30MB
- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` is passed as an environment variable at runtime — NEVER baked into the image
- Templates MUST be embedded in the binary using `//go:embed templates` + `embed.FS` so the container has zero external file dependencies
- The container runs as a non-root user (uid 1001)
- Health check endpoint: `GET /healthz` returns HTTP 200 with `{"status":"ok"}`
- `docker-compose.yml` reads `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` from the host environment and passes it through
- The final story (S7.2) must end with `docker-compose up` successfully serving the app on port 8080

## Go Code Standards
- All exported types and functions MUST have godoc comments
- Error handling: NEVER ignore errors. Every `err != nil` must be handled.
- No `panic()` in production paths — only in `main()` for startup failures
- Use `context.Context` as first argument on any function that does I/O
- Prefer table-driven tests in `_test.go` files alongside source
- All magic numbers must be named constants in the relevant package
- No global mutable state except the session store (which uses sync.RWMutex)
- File size: no Go source file should exceed 300 lines — split if needed

## Critical Safety Rules (never violate)
1. **Bundle size limit:** Reject uploads > `MAX_BUNDLE_MB` (default 250MB) at the HTTP layer before extraction. Return HTTP 413.
2. **Streaming extraction:** Extract tar.gz as a stream — NEVER load the full archive into memory. Use `tar.NewReader(gzip.NewReader(r.Body))`.
3. **Token budget:** The `BundleData` struct passed to Claude must NEVER exceed 80,000 tokens. The parser enforces this by truncating log excerpts.
4. **SSE context propagation:** Every SSE goroutine must `select` on `r.Context().Done()` and return immediately when the client disconnects. No goroutine leaks.
5. **Temp directory cleanup:** Every extracted bundle gets a `defer os.RemoveAll(tmpDir)` AND is registered in the session TTL store for cleanup after 30 minutes.
6. **API key validation at startup:** If `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` is not set, log a warning and enable stub mode — do NOT panic or refuse to start.

## HTML/Template Standards
- Templates are in `templates/` directory, parsed once at startup
- Use `template.Must(template.ParseGlob(...))` with panic on parse failure (startup only)
- All user-provided data must go through `template.HTMLEscapeString()` before rendering
- HTMX attributes use `hx-` prefix as documented at htmx.org
- Tailwind classes only — no custom CSS files. Use CDN: `https://cdn.tailwindcss.com`
- HTMX CDN: `https://unpkg.com/htmx.org@2.0.0`
- HTMX SSE ext CDN: `https://unpkg.com/htmx-ext-sse@2.2.1/sse.js`

## AI / Claude Usage Rules
- Model: always `claude-sonnet-4-6` (claude-sonnet-4-6-20250929 for SDK)
- Max tokens per phase: Phase 1 (triage) = 1024, Phase 2 (timeline) = 2048, Phase 3 (RCA) = 4096, Chat = 2048
- All prompts are defined as constants in `internal/analysis/prompts.go` — never inline prompts in handlers
- Structured outputs (triage, timeline) use JSON mode with explicit schema in the prompt
- RCA and chat use streaming via `client.Messages.NewStreaming()`
- Always pass `context.Context` to SDK calls so they can be cancelled on client disconnect

## Stub Mode
When `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` is empty OR `STUB_MODE=true`:
- Analysis phases return pre-canned responses from `internal/analysis/stubs.go`
- SSE streaming still works (simulated with `time.Sleep` chunks)
- UI shows a yellow "⚠ Stub mode" banner
- This allows the reviewer to run the app without an API key

## Error UX
- HTTP errors render the `templates/error.html` partial, not a blank page
- API errors from Claude show: "Analysis unavailable — [reason]" in the relevant panel
- Upload errors show inline validation messages via HTMX swap
- Server panics are recovered by middleware and return HTTP 500 with a useful message

## Testing Requirements
- `bundle/extract_test.go`: test with a crafted minimal tar.gz, assert file tree
- `bundle/parser_test.go`: test parsing of sample JSON fixtures in `testdata/`
- `analysis/prompts_test.go`: test that rendered prompts stay under token budget
- `session/store_test.go`: test TTL expiry and concurrent access (race detector)
- Run tests with: `go test -race ./...`
